docs.abstract: As more technology creeps into the front seat to help drivers, so too will systems that eavesdrop on and monitor them.
docs.snippet: As more technology creeps into the front seat to help drivers, so too will systems that eavesdrop on and monitor them.
docs.lead_paragraph: The automobile, in American life, has long been a hallmark of freedom. A teenager’s first driver’s license offers freedom from Mom and Dad. A new car and the open road bring the freedom to chase the American dream. But as more technology creeps in to help drivers, so, too, will systems that eavesdrop on and monitor them, necessitated not by convenience but by new safety concerns.

headline.main: Eyes on the Road! (Your Car Is Watching)
headline.print_headline: Cars That Watch the Road, and You
